modules.description: Reads and parses Xen boot parameters passed to a MirageOS unikernel, extracting key-value pairs from a string. Processes data in the form of a single string containing space-separated options. Used to access configuration values such as network settings or storage paths during unikernel initialization.
Returns a lazy, asynchronous representation of the command-line arguments. Operates on string arrays and Lwt promises. Useful for delaying argument access until needed in event-driven applications.
